    "source": {
      "goCharacterKey": "RaidenShogun",
      "note": "Normal/charged/plunging generated from Genshin Optimizer sheets (master) + allStat_gen skillParam. skill.dmg/coorDmg parsed by hand from libs/gi/sheets/src/Characters/RaidenShogun/index.tsx. burst.dmg/hit1-5/charged1-2/plunge/plungeLow/plungeHigh are the Musou no Hitotachi nuke + Musou Isshin-infused NA/CA/Plunge base multipliers (Lv10, Amber talent id 3 params 1/5-16 -- 0 Resolve stacks, NOT baked with any Resolve bonus as of 2026-07-15). All normal/charged/plunging/skill/burst multipliers re-verified byte-for-byte 2026-07-16 against GO's raw libs/gi/stats/Data/Characters/RaidenShogun/skillParam.json (Lv10 = index 9). The Chakra Desiderata Resolve DMG% bonus is modeled as a selectable self_conditional ('burstResolveStacks', see buffs.self_conditional_modifiers_json) instead of a fixed assumption, since GO's own sheet (index.tsx burstResolve()) computes dmg=(mv+resolveBonus)*ATK with resolveBonus = resolveBonus_rate x stacks -- an ABSOLUTE addition to each hit's own mv, not a proportional DMG% bonus, so it can't be a shared 'burst_dmg_'-style key. Each hit instead carries a dedicated mvMultiplierKeys entry (raiden_resolve<Hit>_mult_) read at eval time from stats (default 1.0 = 0 stacks); the conditional's 6 states (10/20/30/40/50/60, matching GO's own UI) set mult = 1 + (resolveBonus_rate x stacks)/mv for that specific hit. resolveBonus1=0.069984/stack (Amber param2, applies only to burst.dmg) and resolveBonus2=0.013071/stack (Amber param3, applies to the other 11 hits) -- verified byte-for-byte against GO's raw skillParam.json burst[1]/burst[2] arrays for all 6 states (10-60 stacks), reproducing the previous unconditional bake exactly at 60 (e.g. hit1: mv 0.798157 x mult 1.982589 = 1.582417). Hit keys match GO target paths; multKey = <hitKey>_mult. Levels: Lv10, C0. A4 'Wishes Unnumbered' (buffs.self_modifiers_json electro_dmg_from_enerRech_ = 0.4) matches GO's passive2ElecDmgBonus node exactly: (ER-100%) x 0.4%. FIXED 2026-07-16: removed a fabricated 'electro_dmg_from_enerRech_cap_: 0.8' (80% cap) that does not exist anywhere in GO's formula (libs/gi/sheets/src/Characters/RaidenShogun/index.tsx has no min()/clamp on passive2ElecDmgBonus) -- the bonus is genuinely uncapped in GO, so it was silently under-valuing Raiden's A4 on any build clearing ~300% ER (achievable with Emblem of Severed Fate + ER sands + ER substats).",
      "assumptions": {
        "constellation": 0,
        "characterLevel": 90,
        "autoTalentLevel": 10,
        "skillTalentLevel": 10,
        "burstTalentLevel": 10,
        "resolveStacks": "selectable via burstResolveStacks self_conditional (default 0 if unselected)"
      }
    }
  },
